All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:

**`Cargo.toml` (workspace)** — added `mime_guess = "2"` to workspace dependencies

**`crates/media/Cargo.toml`** — added `mime_guess = { workspace = true }`

**`crates/media/src/mime.rs`** — replaced the 30-line manual match in `mime_from_extension` with:
```rust
pub fn mime_from_extension(ext: &str) -> Option<&'static str> {
    let lower = ext.to_ascii_lowercase();
    match lower.as_str() {
        "text" | "log" => return Some("text/plain"),
        "ppm" => return Some("image/x-portable-pixmap"),
        _ => {}
    }
    mime_guess::from_ext(&lower).first_raw()
}
```
Only `text`, `log`, and `ppm` need manual overrides — `mime_guess` handles everything else. The function now also supports hundreds more extensions automatically.

**Test updates** — adjusted tests that asserted `bmp`/`svg`/`xyz` return `None` (they're now recognized by `mime_guess`), using `.qqqq` as the truly-unknown extension instead.

`extension_for_mime` is kept manual since it encodes opinionated preferred extensions (e.g. `jpg` not `jpeg`, `bin` as fallback).

